HEADWORD: Cholæmia
<hw>Cho*l⟦ae⟧"mi*a</hw> <pr>(k⟦osl⟧*l⟦emac⟧"m⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>cholh`</grk> bile +
<grk>a"i^ma</grk> blood.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease
characterized by severe nervous symptoms, dependent upon the presence of
the constituents of the bile in the blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

